Here's the **c-avatar** component — an MCSS Atom for displaying user profile images with fallback initials.

---

## HTML

```html
<div
  class="c-avatar"
  typeof="mcs:Component"
  property="mcs:taxonomyLevel" content="mcs:Atom"
  property="mcs:purpose" content="Displays a user profile image with fallback initials"
  data-state="medium"
  data-mcs-interaction-type="hover"
  data-mcs-consequence="Visual feedback on hover"
>
  <img
    class="c-avatar__image"
    src="https://i.pravatar.cc/150?u=john-doe"
    alt="John Doe"
    onerror="this.style.display='none'; this.nextElementSibling.style.display='flex';"
  />
  <span class="c-avatar__initials" aria-hidden="true">JD</span>
</div>
```

---

## CSS

```css
/* =============================================
   c-avatar — Atom
   ============================================= */

/* Root — no margin (Golden Rule) */
.c-avatar {
  position: relative;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  background-color: var(--color-brand-500);
  color: var(--color-text-on-brand);
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
  line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
  overflow: hidden;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  transition: box-shadow var(--transition-fast), opacity var(--transition-fast);
  cursor: default;
}

/* Hover feedback */
.c-avatar:hover {
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  opacity: 0.9;
}

/* Image — fills the container */
.c-avatar__image {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  display: block;
}

/* Initials — hidden by default, shown when image fails */
.c-avatar__initials {
  display: none;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  user-select: none;
}

/* =============================================
   Size variants via data-state
   ============================================= */

/* Small */
.c-avatar[data-state="small"] {
  width: 32px;
  height: 32px;
  font-size: var(--font-size-caption);
}

/* Medium (default) */
.c-avatar[data-state="medium"] {
  width: 48px;
  height: 48px;
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
}

/* Large */
.c-avatar[data-state="large"] {
  width: 72px;
  height: 72px;
  font-size: var(--font-size-title);
}
```

---

## Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| **`data-state` for size** | Follows MCSS state management rule — no class modifiers for variants. `data-state="small|medium|large"` controls dimensions and font size. |
| **Fallback initials** | The `<span>` is hidden by default. When the `<img>` fails to load, its `onerror` hides the image and reveals the initials via `display: flex`. |
| **`aria-hidden="true"` on initials** | Prevents screen readers from announcing both the image alt text and the initials. The `alt` attribute on the image is the authoritative accessible name. |
| **`flex-shrink: 0`** | Prevents the avatar from being compressed in flex layouts (e.g., inside a card header). |
| **`overflow: hidden`** | Ensures the image and initials are clipped to the circular shape created by `border-radius: var(--border-radius-full)`. |
| **No margin on root** | Complies with the Golden Rule — external spacing is the responsibility of layout classes (`l-*`). |
| **Hover interaction** | `data-mcs-interaction-type="hover"` and `data-mcs-consequence` document the behavior for tooling and analysis. |

---

## Usage Example

```html
<!-- Small avatar -->
<div class="c-avatar" data-state="small" typeof="mcs:Component" ...>
  <img class="c-avatar__image" src="..." alt="Jane Smith" onerror="..." />
  <span class="c-avatar__initials">JS</span>
</div>

<!-- Large avatar with no image (initials only) -->
<div class="c-avatar" data-state="large" typeof="mcs:Component" ...>
  <img class="c-avatar__image" src="broken.jpg" alt="Alex Lee" onerror="..." style="display:none" />
  <span class="c-avatar__initials" style="display:flex">AL</span>
</div>
```

