## c-badge Component

### HTML

```html
<div
  class="c-badge"
  typeof="mcs:Component"
  property="mcs:taxonomyLevel" content="mcs:Atom"
  property="mcs:purpose" content="Displays a compact status indicator with semantic color states"
  data-state="default"
  data-mcs-interaction-type="none"
  data-mcs-consequence="Visually communicates the status or category of an associated element"
>
  <span class="c-badge__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Status Label</span>
</div>
```

### CSS

```css
/* =============================================
   c-badge — Status Indicator Atom
   Layer: Component (c-*)
   ============================================= */

.c-badge {
  /* Layout */
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-1);

  /* Sizing */
  padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-2);

  /* Typography */
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-caption);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
  line-height: var(--line-height-tight);

  /* Visual */
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  background-color: var(--color-background-primary);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);

  /* Interaction */
  user-select: none;
  cursor: default;

  /* Animation */
  transition:
    background-color var(--transition-fast),
    border-color var(--transition-fast),
    color var(--transition-fast);
}

/* --- Elements --- */

.c-badge__dot {
  display: inline-block;
  width: var(--space-2);
  height: var(--space-2);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  background-color: currentColor;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.c-badge__label {
  white-space: nowrap;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
  max-width: 12ch;
}

/* --- Semantic Color States (via data-state) --- */

/* Default / Info */
.c-badge[data-state="default"],
.c-badge[data-state="info"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-primary);
  border-color: var(--color-border-interactive);
  color: var(--color-text-link);
}

/* Success */
.c-badge[data-state="success"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-success);
  border-color: var(--color-border-success);
  color: var(--color-text-success);
}

/* Warning */
.c-badge[data-state="warning"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-warning);
  border-color: var(--color-yellow-500);
  color: var(--color-text-warning);
}

/* Error */
.c-badge[data-state="error"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-error);
  border-color: var(--color-border-error);
  color: var(--color-text-error);
}

/* --- Variants (via class modifiers) --- */

/* Pill variant — more rounded, larger padding */
.c-badge--pill {
  padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-3);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
}

/* Outline variant — transparent background, thicker border */
.c-badge--outline {
  background-color: transparent;
  border-width: 2px;
}

/* Dot-only variant — hides label, shows only dot */
.c-badge--dot-only .c-badge__label {
  display: none;
}

.c-badge--dot-only .c-badge__dot {
  width: var(--space-3);
  height: var(--space-3);
}

/* --- Sizes (via class modifiers) --- */

.c-badge--sm {
  padding: 2px var(--space-1);
  font-size: var(--font-size-overline);
}

.c-badge--sm .c-badge__dot {
  width: var(--space-1);
  height: var(--space-1);
}

.c-badge--lg {
  padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
}

.c-badge--lg .c-badge__dot {
  width: var(--space-3);
  height: var(--space-3);
}

/* --- Accessibility --- */

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .c-badge {
    transition: none;
  }
}

/* High contrast mode support */
@media (forced-colors: active) {
  .c-badge {
    border: 2px solid ButtonText;
  }
  .c-badge__dot {
    background-color: ButtonText;
  }
}
```

### Usage Examples

```html
<!-- Success badge -->
<div class="c-badge" data-state="success">
  <span class="c-badge__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Completed</span>
</div>

<!-- Warning pill badge -->
<div class="c-badge c-badge--pill" data-state="warning">
  <span class="c-badge__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Pending Review</span>
</div>

<!-- Error outline badge (small) -->
<div class="c-badge c-badge--outline c-badge--sm" data-state="error">
  <span class="c-badge__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Failed</span>
</div>

<!-- Info dot-only badge -->
<div class="c-badge c-badge--dot-only" data-state="info">
  <span class="c-badge__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">New Feature</span>
</div>
```

## Design Decisions

1. **Semantic states via `data-state`**: Following MCSS state management rules, all color variants use `data-state` attributes (`success`, `warning`, `error`, `info`). This keeps the component extensible and accessible.

2. **Dot + Label structure**: The badge uses two child elements — a visual dot indicator and a text label. The dot uses `aria-hidden="true"` since it's decorative, while the label provides the semantic content.

3. **No margin on root**: The `c-badge` root class declares no margin, adhering to the Golden Rule. External spacing is handled by layout classes (`l-*`).

4. **Token-driven values**: All colors, spacing, typography, and border-radius values use CSS custom properties from the design token system. No magic numbers.

5. **Modifier variants**: Size (`--sm`, `--lg`) and style (`--pill`, `--outline`, `--dot-only`) are handled via BEM class modifiers, while state remains in `data-state`.

6. **Accessibility**: Includes `prefers-reduced-motion` support and forced-colors mode for high contrast environments. The component is non-interactive (`data-mcs-interaction-type="none"`), as badges are purely presentational.

Here's the **c-button** component — an MCSS Atom with four variants and three states, fully token-driven and RDFa annotated.

---

## HTML

```html
<button
  class="c-button"
  typeof="mcs:Component"
  property="mcs:taxonomyLevel" content="mcs:Atom"
  property="mcs:purpose" content="Triggers an action or event"
  data-variant="primary"
  data-state="default"
  data-mcs-interaction-type="click"
  data-mcs-consequence="Initiates the associated action"
  data-mcs-triggers-event="button:click"
>
  <span class="c-button__label">Submit</span>
  <span class="c-button__spinner" hidden aria-hidden="true">
    <span class="c-spinner"></span>
  </span>
</button>
```

---

## CSS

```css
/* ============================================ */
/* c-button — Atom                              */
/* ============================================ */

/* Root — no margin (Golden Rule) */
.c-button {
  /* Layout & sizing */
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  gap: var(--space-2);
  padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-5);
  border: 2px solid transparent;
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
  cursor: pointer;
  user-select: none;

  /* Typography */
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
  line-height: var(--line-height-base);

  /* Transitions */
  transition:
    background-color var(--transition-base),
    border-color var(--transition-base),
    color var(--transition-base),
    box-shadow var(--transition-base),
    opacity var(--transition-base);

  /* Focus ring */
  outline: none;
}

.c-button:focus-visible {
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--color-border-focus);
}

/* ============================================ */
/* Variants (data-variant)                      */
/* ============================================ */

/* Primary */
.c-button[data-variant="primary"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-brand);
  color: var(--color-text-on-brand);
  border-color: var(--color-background-brand);
}

.c-button[data-variant="primary"]:hover {
  background-color: var(--color-background-brand-hover);
  border-color: var(--color-background-brand-hover);
}

/* Secondary */
.c-button[data-variant="secondary"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-secondary);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  border-color: var(--color-border-interactive);
}

.c-button[data-variant="secondary"]:hover {
  background-color: var(--color-gray-100);
  border-color: var(--color-brand-500);
}

/* Outline */
.c-button[data-variant="outline"] {
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--color-text-link);
  border-color: var(--color-border-interactive);
}

.c-button[data-variant="outline"]:hover {
  background-color: var(--color-brand-50);
  border-color: var(--color-brand-500);
}

/* Ghost */
.c-button[data-variant="ghost"] {
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--color-text-link);
  border-color: transparent;
}

.c-button[data-variant="ghost"]:hover {
  background-color: var(--color-brand-50);
}

/* ============================================ */
/* States (data-state)                          */
/* ============================================ */

/* Loading */
.c-button[data-state="loading"] {
  pointer-events: none;
  opacity: 0.7;
}

.c-button[data-state="loading"] .c-button__label {
  visibility: hidden;
}

.c-button[data-state="loading"] .c-button__spinner {
  visibility: visible;
  position: absolute;
}

/* Disabled */
.c-button[data-state="disabled"] {
  pointer-events: none;
  opacity: 0.4;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}

/* Error */
.c-button[data-state="error"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-error);
  color: var(--color-text-on-brand);
  border-color: var(--color-border-error);
}

.c-button[data-state="error"]:hover {
  background-color: var(--color-red-800);
  border-color: var(--color-red-800);
}

/* ============================================ */
/* Elements                                     */
/* ============================================ */

.c-button__label {
  display: inline-block;
}

.c-button__spinner {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
}

/* ============================================ */
/* Utility: full-width modifier                 */
/* ============================================ */

.c-button--full {
  width: 100%;
}
```

---

## Usage Examples

```html
<!-- Primary (default) -->
<button class="c-button" data-variant="primary" data-state="default">Save</button>

<!-- Secondary, disabled -->
<button class="c-button" data-variant="secondary" data-state="disabled">Cancel</button>

<!-- Outline, loading -->
<button class="c-button" data-variant="outline" data-state="loading">Processing…</button>

<!-- Ghost, error -->
<button class="c-button" data-variant="ghost" data-state="error">Delete</button>
```

---

## Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| **`data-variant` instead of class modifiers** | Keeps the component taxonomy clean; variants are semantic attributes, not visual classes. |
| **`data-state` for loading/disabled/error** | Follows MCSS state management rule — no `.c-button--loading` class. |
| **Spinner element inside button** | Loading state hides the label and shows a positioned spinner, preserving button dimensions. |
| **No margin on root** | Golden Rule — external spacing is the responsibility of `l-*` layout classes. |
| **All values via `var()`** | Zero magic numbers; every color, space, radius, and font token is referenced from the design token set. |
| **Focus-visible ring** | Uses `--color-border-focus` for accessible keyboard navigation without cluttering default state. |
| **Full-width modifier** | Only modifier allowed (`.c-button--full`) because it's a layout concern, not a variant or state. |

