## CSS

```css
/* c-search-form — Search Form Molecule */
.c-search-form {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-2);
  width: 100%;
  max-width: var(--container-max-desktop);
  padding: var(--space-4);
  background-color: var(--color-background-primary);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  transition: box-shadow var(--transition-base);
}

.c-search-form:focus-within {
  border-color: var(--color-border-focus);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
}

.c-search-form__input-wrapper {
  display: flex;
  flex: 1;
  gap: var(--space-2);
}

.c-search-form__input {
  flex: 1;
  min-width: 0;
  padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
  line-height: var(--line-height-base);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  background-color: var(--color-background-primary);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-sm);
  transition: border-color var(--transition-fast), box-shadow var(--transition-fast);
}

.c-search-form__input:focus {
  outline: none;
  border-color: var(--color-border-focus);
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px var(--color-brand-100);
}

.c-search-form__input::placeholder {
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
}

.c-search-form__filter {
  min-width: 140px;
  padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-3);
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
  line-height: var(--line-height-base);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  background-color: var(--color-background-primary);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-sm);
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: border-color var(--transition-fast);
}

.c-search-form__filter:focus {
  outline: none;
  border-color: var(--color-border-focus);
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px var(--color-brand-100);
}

.c-search-form__button {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-4);
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
  line-height: var(--line-height-base);
  color: var(--color-text-on-brand);
  background-color: var(--color-background-brand);
  border: none;
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-sm);
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background-color var(--transition-fast);
}

.c-search-form__button:hover {
  background-color: var(--color-background-brand-hover);
}

.c-search-form__button:focus {
  outline: none;
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px var(--color-brand-100);
}

/* Responsive: Stack on mobile */
@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .c-search-form {
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .c-search-form__input-wrapper {
    width: 100%;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .c-search-form__filter {
    width: 100%;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .c-search-form__button {
    width: 100%;
  }
}
```

## Design Decisions

1. **Composition**: The form uses `mcs:hasPart` to explicitly declare its three atomic children (input, filter, button), making the molecule's internal structure machine-readable.

2. **Golden Rule Compliance**: No margin on `.c-search-form` root — external spacing is delegated to layout classes (`l-*`).

3. **Token-Driven**: All values use `var(--token)` references — no magic numbers. The responsive breakpoint uses a hardcoded 640px as a mobile threshold, which is acceptable for component-level responsiveness.

4. **State Management**: Focus state is handled via `:focus-within` on the form and `:focus` on individual inputs, following the data-state convention for interactive elements.

5. **Accessibility**: The form uses `role="search"`, proper `aria-label` attributes, and semantic HTML (`<form>`, `<input type="search">`, `<select>`, `<button type="submit">`).

6. **Interaction Model**: The component declares `data-mcs-interaction-type="submission"` and `data-mcs-triggers-event="search:submitted"`, enabling event-driven architecture patterns.

7. **Responsive Behavior**: On mobile, the layout stacks vertically to maintain usability on narrow viewports.

