3. **Aria integration** — The input includes `aria-invalid="true"` and `aria-describedby` pointing to the error message `<p>` with `role="alert"`, ensuring accessibility for screen readers.

4. **Cascading error styling** — The error state also affects the label and message colors via `var(--color-text-error)`, creating a cohesive error visual system.

5. **No margin on root** — The `.c-input` root uses `gap` for internal spacing, respecting the Golden Rule. External spacing is left to layout (`l-*`) classes.

